#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:154
#, no-wrap
msgid "Benefits of GBIF Participation"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:161
msgid "In building a case for a country or international organization to join GBIF, you will need to explain the benefits of GBIF Participation and of establishing a node.  In 2019, during GBIF's Governing Board meeting, the GBIF Participants were asked to provide statements on how they summarize GBIF‚Äôs value and communicate it to colleagues and funders.  A selection of the answers given are provided here for you to review and compare.  Consider which benefits of Participation are common across the statements and which are unique to the specific Participant concerned.  You can find further information about each GBIF Participant delegation by following the links to the country pages on the GBIF website."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block *
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:164
msgid "[NOTE.documentation] Read these statements from GBIF Participants on how they communicate GBIF‚Äôs value, and consider how they relate to the context of your country or organization."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "üá¶üá∫{nbsp}https://www.gbif.org/country/AU/summary[Australia^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:170
msgid "The major biodiversity assessment and monitoring challenges confronting nations are inherently transnational and thus demand data at such scale.  The Global Biodiversity Information Facility delivers three key functions for Australia."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:172
msgid "First, it provides the national and global biodiversity research community access to the best available transnational data to support their work."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:173
msgid "Second, it provides a global focal point to foster data interoperability, promulgation of data standards and architectural alignment, which inherently leads to a smoother flow of data."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:175
msgid "And finally it allows Australian biodiversity data generated by collections, museums, researchers, ecological monitoring and citizen science programs to deliver impact globally.  Conversely, it allows Australian researchers and decision makers access to data that would be otherwise hard to obtain for purposes such as biosecurity risk assessment and climate change scenario planning."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:177
msgid "GBIF has achieved what few other environmental domains have been able to achieve globally and acts as a strong exemplar to scientific and research funding infrastructure initiatives of the level of coordination and cooperation within the biodiversity domain."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:179
#, no-wrap
msgid "üáßüá™{nbsp}https://www.gbif.org/country/BE/summary[Belgium^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:185
msgid "GBIF is a unique infrastructure delivering access to a vast quantity of evidence data from various sources (specimens, observations, monitoring).  It is a fantastic indexation tool for biodiversity data.  It provides a powerful common denominator aggregating data tool."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:187
msgid "Thanks to capacity enhancement programmes and numerous training workshops, GBIF\tsucceeded to create a vibrant community of nodes supporting data publishers and users around the globe."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:189
msgid "GBIF‚Äôs Data Citation mechanism is amongst the most advanced in open data and open science landscape."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "üá®üá¶{nbsp}https://www.gbif.org/country/CA/summary[Canada^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:195
msgid "In communicating the value of GBIF to colleagues and funders, Canada emphasizes that:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:197
msgid "GBIF provides Canadian citizens and stakeholders with an easy, reliable one-stop source available anywhere for accessing Canadian and global biodiversity information, wherever the data was generated;"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:198
msgid "GBIF provides great added value from the perspective that it facilitates aggregating relevant data from different sources and reviewing data quality which can be very labour-intensive."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:199
msgid "Like many other countries, the Government of Canada committed to an Open Government Strategy. Membership in GBIF and contribution of Canadian biodiversity datasets directly supports Open Government activities."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:201
msgid "Participation in GBIF also contributes to Canada‚Äôs data and information requirements for Canadian commitments to intergovernmental processes.  For example, having detailed biodiversity data contributes to the Convention for Biological Diversity‚Äôs Aichi Target 19 on the sharing of biodiversity knowledge and also on target 9 (invasive species), target 11 (protected areas), target 12 (avoiding extinctions), and target 13 (conserving genetic resources)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:203
#, no-wrap
msgid "üá¨üá≠{nbsp}https://www.gbif.org/country/GH/summary[Ghana^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:207
msgid "I would like to summarize the value proposition of GBIF for Ghana in four ways:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:209
msgid "GBIF is an international community and / infrastructure of excellence that is truly dedicated to serving open biodiversity data for science, conservation and policy."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:210
msgid "GBIF is an excellent practitioner of the ‚Äúnew‚Äù and existing discipline of biodiversity informatics."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:211
msgid "GBIF is a means to achieving national commitments to inter-governmental cooperation / agreements such as Clearing House Mechanisms (CHM) of the CBD."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:212
msgid "GBIF is a powerful aggregator of worldwide biodiversity data that is crucial for biodiversity research and science."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "üáÆüá™{nbsp}https://www.gbif.org/country/IE/summary[Ireland^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:219
msgid "To summarize GBIF‚Äôs value from Ireland‚Äôs perspective:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:221
msgid "It internationalizes Ireland‚Äôs work ‚Äì being a small island the temptation for us is to have a national focus ‚Äì GBIF allows us to participate easily and proactively in a global initiative/network with all the benefits that this brings"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:223
msgid "Through Ireland‚Äôs participation in GBIF it ensures that knowledge on the spatial distribution of Irish biodiversity contributes to the global biodiversity database, - important that we are not overlooked!"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:225
msgid "It provides a valuable and good value for money resource for researchers within, and associated with, Ireland to use in biodiversity related research, thereby improving the evidence base on Ireland‚Äôs biodiversity and how it is changing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:227
#, no-wrap
msgid "üá∞üá∑{nbsp}https://www.gbif.org/country/KR/summary[Korea, Republic of^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:231
msgid "The data from Korean Biodiversity need to be registered and distributed through the GBIF‚Äôs integrated portal to manage and secure strategically the national biological resources. It is also necessary to respond to international issues of ABS* by following the Korea‚Äôs ratification in May 2017 on the Nagoya Protocol. In summary, I would like to say that the GBIF‚Äôs values are to collect and share the original data and samples of biological resources to people, and then they can use them for various purposes of environmental monitoring, biodiversity management & conservation, and further industrial uses in medicines, cosmetics, health functional foods, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:232
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Nagoya Protocol on Access to Genetic Resources and the Fair and Equitable Sharing of Benefits Arising from Their Utilization to the Convention on Biological Diversity"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:235
#, no-wrap
msgid "üá≤üáΩ{nbsp}https://www.gbif.org/country/MX/summary[Mexico^]"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:242
msgid "GBIF is the most comprehensive source of free spatial biodiversity information in the world, really important since biodiversity does not recognize political frontiers and many analysis need to include the whole range of species distribution, assess invasive species, changes caused by climate change or other drivers.  Having access to those data has proved to be very useful tool, despite we might like to have additional data on species population, for example, to assess endangered species.  For many megadiverse countries, this infrastructure provides the basic information needed for better decisions, that provide opportunities for collaboration in different ways.  GBIF has already proved its value."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: case-for-participation.en.adoc:244
#, no-wrap
msgid "üáµüáπ{nbsp}https://www.gbif.org/country/PT/summary[Portugal^]"
